It seems not everyone in the Western Cape received the memo about the ban on cigarette sales and government's mixed messages have made matters even more confusing. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - It seems not everyone in the Western Cape received the memo about the ban on cigarette sales. Earlier this week, the provincial government announced cigarettes could be bought as part of essential goods shopping. They went from thinking they can no longer buy cigarettes to hearing they can, only to be told the ban is still in place during the lockdown. READ: Smokers can get cigarettes in Western Cape But this was quickly squashed by police minister Bheki Cele. Watch the video above for more on this story.